Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Finely chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1}(stalks and all) and pop into a #medium bowl{} with the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the marinade. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and mix together.

Add the @Skin-On British Chicken Breasts{2} to the #bowl{} and mix to coat well.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan, skin-side down. Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Meanwhile, chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the @Green Beans{150%g}.

Pop the potatoes onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the middle shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once seared, transfer the chicken to another #baking tray{}, skin-side up, then roast on the top shelf until cooked, ~{18-25%minutes}.

When the chicken is cooked, transfer to a #board{} to rest for a couple of mins loosely covered in #foil{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Sticky Sauce ==

While everything roasts, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop into a bowl with the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Mango Chutney{40%g} and the @Water{2%tbsp} for the sauce. Mix together your sticky sauce and set aside.

== Vegetables ==

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{2%tsp}.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil.

Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

== Finishing ==

Meanwhile, once the potatoes have roasted, add the sticky sauce and @Chorizo{60%g}(diced) to the tray and mix together until well coated.

Lay the @Chopped Kale{100%g} on top, drizzle with a little @oil{2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> TIP: Remove any tough stalks from the kale.

Return the tray to your oven and bake until the kale is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When everything is ready, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm slices.

Add the green beans to the veg tray and mix together with the potatoes, kale and chorizo, then share between your plates. Top with the herby chicken. Enjoy!

> Step 5 MOD: If you've chosen to add diced chorizo to your meal, add to the potato baking tray when you add the sticky sauce and mix together until well coated. Then add the kale and continue as instructed.